<br>
What you need to do is get all - I mean all - of the druids/wizs who like to raid trained as transport officers. This means when a target of opportunity does pop-up there should be a couple on who can rush to helping pick people up.<br>
<br>
Generally those who have the ability to port around quickly are much more willing to go after the targets of opportunity - which I agree tend to be the order of the day. And they are also more aware of how to get around as they have been playing a class for a year that easily gets them to any zone.<br>
<br>
If they are additionally given the job as port officer for every raid they would get very effecient at grabbing people.<br>
<br>
This theory would extend to everyone who attends raids. I won't go over all the possible jobs, but others should have some sort of organizational/leadership task asigned to them that stays consistent from raid to raid.<br>
<br>
Consistency and understanding one's role makes for a much more efficient, mobile, quick-reacting, blitzkrieging, elite...ok getting carried away <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   ... force that can react to targets of opportunity as they pop-up.<br>
<br>
